images.title: Exploring a lesser-known Tassie gem
images.caption: Exploring a lesser-known Tassie gem
images.desc: While Tasmania is already known for its beautiful coastal views and popular tourist spots like Mona and Cradle Mountain, you should also add Mt. William National Park to the list. Found on the state’s northeast coast, this hidden gem packs plenty of scenic walks including a 90-minute return trek to the park’s summit where you’re likely to encounter much of the natural wildlife. From Tasmanian devils to wombats, many creatures call this land their home. If you’re lucky, you might even spot one of the locals found on today’s homepage.
